Deep Learning vs Machine Learning

| Feature           | Machine Learning                            | Deep Learning                     |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Definition        | AI system learns from data using algorithms | Advanced ML using neural networks |
| Human Involvement | Human gives features manually               | Learns features automatically     |
| Data Requirement  | Small or medium data is enough              | Needs very large data             |
| Training Speed    | Faster                                      | Slower                            |
| Hardware Need     | Normal computer works                       | Powerful GPU/computer needed      |
| Accuracy          | Good for simple tasks                       | Better for complex tasks          |
| Best For          | Prediction & classification                 | Images, speech, AI chatbots       |
| Examples          | Loan prediction, spam detection             | Face recognition, ChatGPT         |
| Algorithms        | Decision Tree, Random Forest                | CNN, RNN, LSTM, Transformer       |
| Complexity        | Simple                                      | More complex                      |
